	   <tr><td colspan=2>kill kill kill. all trades require money to put into them, then after a while you will start making money, im level 31 and im still broke. i think i might have 30 plat to my name. granted i have a full suit of fine plate, ghoulbane, and some nice magical armor as well, but im broke. at 15 you can easily kill willow wisps. and turn in the GLS's to the gypse in karana, or oasis. at 15 you should already be in oasis killing orcs. you can avg about 1 plat per loot there. once you hit 20ish head to OOT from the doc in oasis. the first island you get to has some ogres on it. they drop ok weapons and the armor they drop will sell for several plat each. (its very heavy) this will make you faction with ogres worse but if your roleplaying it does not matter they must all die anyways. at 20 you can also go to a island off of the ogre island where bandits hang out. these bandits will drop some fine steel weapons they can sell of rabout 5 plat each. you need at least 1 friend to go there. you will not make money with arrows. you can try tailoring and make 10 slot back packs i think they for for around 75 plat or so. smithing has some nice money but costs a bloody fortune to get your skill up.<br>i dont mean to sound like a bummer but in the early stages of your career you will be poor. i still am but i tend to always have enough cash on me to buy what i need when i see it auctioned. dont worry same will happen for you. <br><br>&nbsp;<br>Celtpirate Waverider<br>34 paladin<br>saryrn-Boche Morte<br>Yoshiro<br>15 cleric<br>saryrn-House of Wargoth</td></tr>
